Key Match Events: Kai Havertz scored the opening goal for Germany in the 1st minute.
Florian Wirtz scored for Germany in the 49th minute.
Julian Nagelsmann made a tactical substitution in the 60th minute.
Adrien Rabiot scored for France in the 73rd minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Julian Nagelsmann confirmed that Kai Havertz would start as a striker against France.
Nagelsmann praised Havertz's development under Mikel Arteta at Arsenal.
Nagelsmann revealed that Maximilian Mittelstadt would earn his first international cap at left-back.
Nagelsmann confirmed that Manuel Neuer would be Germany's number-one goalkeeper for Euro 2024 despite his recent injury.
